{{ 'ka-collection-breadcrumb.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

{%- comment -%}
  K&A FAQ Breadcrumb
  Spec: Docs/faq-build-spec.md, Section 3 ("S1 — Breadcrumb").
  Verbatim reuse of .ka-coll-breadcrumb (assets/ka-collection-breadcrumb.css)
  per the spec's own explicit instruction — same quiet wayfinding strip
  already used on Collection, with this page's own two-level trail:
  "Home / Frequently Asked Questions". Loading ka-collection-breadcrumb.css
  again here is a harmless duplicate <link> on this page only (browsers
  dedupe), not a new stylesheet — same accepted pattern already documented
  in ka-nav.liquid for ka-collection-grid.css.

  This file also inherits that stylesheet's #ka-nav override, which is
  redundant-but-harmless on this page: the settled/crystallised nav state
  is already applied unconditionally to every non-home template via the
  is_home check in sections/ka-nav.liquid (`ka-nav--settled` unless
  request.page_type == 'index'), confirmed by reading that file directly.
  No separate override is actually required for FAQ to render with a
  permanently-settled nav — it already does, automatically, being a
  non-index page template. Kept for consistency with the spec's explicit
  "verbatim reuse" instruction; it is a no-op layered on top of the
  correct existing mechanism, not a second competing one.
{%- endcomment -%}

<div class="ka-coll-breadcrumb">
  <div class="ka-coll-breadcrumb__inner">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span class="ka-coll-breadcrumb__sep">/</span>
    <span class="ka-coll-breadcrumb__current">Frequently Asked Questions</span>
  </div>
</div>

